cyclone.name: ARLENE
cyclone.current_location: about 285 miles W of Ft. Myers, Florida
cyclone.trajectory: moving southward, then southeastward, away from the northern Gulf Coast toward the central Gulf of Mexico where it is forecast to dissipate
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: No landfall is forecast; system expected to remain over the open central Gulf and degenerate into a remnant low

weather_observation.impacted_coast: Central Gulf waters and portions of the Florida Peninsula (rainfall), not the Louisiana coast
weather_observation.wind: Minimal winds expected; below tropical storm force
weather_observation.rainfall: No significant rainfall expected from ARLENE at the port
